National Industrial Art Exhibition Opens 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 23 (KCNA) -- A national industrial art exhibition opened with due ceremony at the Three-Revolution Exhibition Thursday in celebration of the 60th anniversary of the Workers' Party of Korea.
 It drew at least 800 art studios such as the Industrial Art Studio of the Ministry of Machine-Building, the Light-Industrial Art Studio of the Ministry of Light Industry, the Mansudae Art Studio, Pyongyang University of Fine Art and the Pyongyang Cosmetics Factory, educational institutions and factories and enterprises.  
 On display there are at least 1,200 designs of different kinds of heavy and light industrial products, architectural and environmental decorations, packing goods, advertisements of goods and others and more than 520 manufactured goods and "February 2 products". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also displayed there are designs of brands examined by leader Kim Jong Il and designs of different varieties and types of machines including those of "Naenara" 24 h.p. tractor and "June 15" electric locomotive. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Attracting the interest of visitors are designs of modern light industrial goods such as those of Korean dresses for different ages and seasons, those of graceful and peculiar silk with diverse patterns and colors, those of materials for dresses and those of silk for quilt and their products. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also on display there are designs for decorating the inside and outside of Pyongyang Conservatory, a blueprint of the monument to the Youth Hero Motorway, designs of theaters and cultural halls, those of different kinds of fountains and those of street decorations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also drawing the attention of visitors are attractive packing designs such as those of plastic packing of processed potato and processed goat milk and other designs of brands. 
 Among those present at the opening ceremony were Secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea Choe Thae Bok, Vice-Premier of the Cabinet Ro Tu Chol and officials concerned.

GNP Ultra-Right Conservatives' Reckless Remarks under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 23 (KCNA) -- The ultra-right conservatives of the Grand National Party of south Korea including its floor leader dared pull up the north over south Korea's progressive forces' call for the removal of the statue of MacArthur in Inchon. As regards the north's claim to the legitimate right to the use of nuclear energy for a peaceful purpose at the six-party talks they even let loose a string of balderdash describing it as a far-fetched assertion.
 A spokesman for the Central Committee of the Democratic Front for the Reunification of the Fatherland in a statement on Sept. 22 noted that the GNP's outcries pleasing the U.S. and inciting confrontation with the north are intended to egg the pro-U.S. ultra-right conservative forces on to dampen the spirit of alliance with the north and independence rapidly mounting in south Korea, turn the trend of the times favorable for toeing the U.S. line and pursuing confrontation with the north and save its foundation from its collapse. The statement went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The GNP is no more than a group of philistines who have already lost the worth of its existence. The ridiculous remarks made by the floor leader of the GNP are no more than rubbish of the guy breathing his last, washed away by a violent trend. 
The June 15 era of reunification does not allow any political force going against national reconciliation and reunification to stay in this land. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If the south Korean politicians truly want to live as righteous politicians for national independence and reunification, they should throw away the signboard of the GNP, a symbol of shame and disgrace, and resolutely break with pro-U.S., ultra-right forces.

Taean Friendship Glass Factory Builders and Members of Chinese Del. Meet 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 23 (KCNA) -- Builders of the Taean Friendship Glass Factory had a meeting with members of the visiting delegation of the All-China Federation of Trade Unions headed by Vice-Chairman Wang Ruixiang at the construction site of the factory on Sept. 22.
 Ryang Jang Gyun, vice-minister of Construction and Building-Materials Industries, and Kim Myong Gi, chairman of the Trade Union Committee of the factory, in their speeches said that leader Kim Jong Il is directing meticulous concern to the glass factory aided by the Chinese government so that it would be built successfully as a symbol of the DPRK-China friendship, expressing their will to make positive efforts to successfully complete the construction of the factory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that cooperation between the two countries has tradition, Wang Ruixiang hoped that the factory, a symbol of the Sino-DPRK friendship, would be completed to contribute to the living of the Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Before the meeting, the Chinese guests went round the melting workshop, the moulding workshop and other production processes.

Anniversary of Kim Il Sung's Work Marked 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 23 (KCNA) -- A national meeting was held at the People's Palace of Culture Friday to mark the 40th anniversary of President Kim Il Sung's famous work "To Give Full Play to the Great Vitality of the Unified and Detailed Planning of the National Economy." 
 The President put forth in the work a unique idea and policy on the planning of the socialist economy. Principled issues arising in stepping up the planning are expounded in the work. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Kwang Rin, chairman of the State Planning Commission, in a report said that the idea and theory on the unified and detailed planning of national economy has made it possible to thoroughly establish Juche in planning the national economy, materialize the monolithic leadership of the party and the leader over the economic development, decisively intensify the state planned guidance, fully tap the creative ingenuity of broad producer masses and thus pave the way for giving full play to the advantages of the socialist economy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Saying that the planning of the national economy has been steadily improved under the energetic leadership of Kim Jong Il, he went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il has clarified the seed of improving the economic management as required by the Songun era and wisely led the officials of economic guidance to thoroughly implement the party's policy of the unified and detailed planning and successfully apply the principles of planned management and operation based on collectivism.
 The policy of the unified and detailed planning has been successfully implemented in the past, big changes have been made in the socialist economic construction, state centralized guidance over the socialist economy and the mass line have been properly applied and the work of planning the national economy has been converted into that of the producer masses themselves. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He called on all the officials of economic guidance and planning to solve the economic management problems our own way with the firm confidence in the advantages of the socialist planned economy, steadily improve the planning of the national economy and give fuller play to the might and invincible vitality of the socialist planned economy.
 The meeting was attended by Pak Pong Ju, Choe Yong Rim, Kwak Pom Gi, Ro Tu Chol and other officials concerned.

Measure Committee for Retaking Monument to Victory Inaugurated 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 23 (KCNA) -- The Measure Committee for Retaking the Monument to the Victory in the Battles in the Northern Area of Korea was formed with Kim Sok Hwan, director of the Bureau for Direction of Cultural Preservation, as its chairman.
 A meeting was held by authorities and public organizations concerned in the DPRK including the Bureau for Direction of Cultural Preservation, the Korean Buddhist Federation, the Academy of Social Sciences and the Secretariat of the Committee for the Peaceful Reunification of the Fatherland in Pyongyang on Sept. 21 to recover the monument. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The meeting decided to form the committee to actively push forward the work. 
 The monument has a record of the historical facts that the Korean volunteer army defeated the Japanese intruders into the area of Hamgyong Province of Korea in the period of the Imjin Patriotic War (1592-1598). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 When the Japanese aggression army invaded Korea in 1904 under the pretext of Russo-Japanese war, Ikeda, commanding officer of the army, saw the monument standing in Rimmyongyok (now Kim Chaek City) of North Hamgyong Province in 1905. At that time he grumbled that such monument standing there would touch off strong anti-Japanese sentiment among Koreans and this would not be in favor of Japan's enforcement of the rule of colonial enslavement over Korea. Then it was shipped to Tokyo in secrecy in 1906. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese aggressors considered the monument too wonderful and excellent in its stone material and sculptural art to destroy it. It has thus been preserved up to this date as "a trophy" from their colony. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What is more serious is that it is now left in a corner of the "Yasukuni Shrine." 
 The monument taken away by the Japanese imperialists from the northern area of Korea at that time is the Korean nation's precious artifact of great historical value.

Ullim Falls of "Arirang"
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 23 (KCNA) -- The Scene 1 of the Act 3 of the ongoing mass gymnastic and artistic performance "Arirang" represents the Ullim Falls, one of the eight scenic spots which have come into being in the Democratic People's Republic of Korea in the Songun era.
 The eight fairies of a legend, that they descended to Mt. Kumgang once upon a time, dance down from the heaven to the Ullim Falls to enjoy its beauty under the eyes of a cowboy on a specially made stage while beautiful mountains and streams are drawn on the background by the effect of laser rays. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The scenery of the falls sending up clouds of spray and making loud sound echo and the landscape of surrounding mountains are depicted by the stage setting (84m�~25m) and the background (180m�~35m) with the help of colorful illumination.
 On the ground dancers in flower-like clothes form a sea of flower while the fairies joyously dance on the special stage, representing the Korean people enjoying a happy life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 When Hyangbal Dance reflecting the joy of the fairies is at its zenith, pictures and words �gRest homes for people are found everywhere�h and �gSanatoria for people are found everywhere�h appear on the background, making the audience feel great happiness of living in the beautiful land. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The fairies, who do not want to leave the falls, send only their flying clothes to the sky and live a happy life along with the people in this land. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Each scene of the work well reflects the beautiful country, a people's paradise good to live in where eight sceneries have been created in the Songun era.

Gastropod Shell Pictures Famous in Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 23 (KCNA) -- Gastropod shell pictures created in the Democratic People's Republic of Korea are drawing special attention of experts and working people for their unique method of depiction and creative skill.
 The pictures delicately representing the original ones with the natural color of gastropod shells give people graceful and comfortable feelings. Their colors remain unchanged even after many years. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is a kind of art pieces which has developed in its own inherent form since the first gastropod shell picture was created in Haeju, South Hwanghae Province more than 30 years ago. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The Saegori Producer's Co-operative in Haeju City, South Hwanghae Province, is specialized in creating gastropod shell pictures. It, keeping the features of the pictures alive, is producing various themes of gastropod shell art pieces including landscape and figure pictures to suit the taste of people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, the cooperative also creates flower-vases, crocodile, turtle and other handiworks decorated with gastropod shell. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Sin Son Bi, a competent creator of the co-operative, told KCNA world-famous pictures including Mona Lisa that were reproduced with natural gastropod shells are popular in Asia, Europe and other regions.

Kim Jong Il Enjoys Art Performance
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 23 (KCNA) -- Supreme Commander of the Korean People's Army Kim Jong Il, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea and chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission, together with KPA servicepersons, enjoyed an art performance given by the art squads of KPA Units 966 and 337.
 Among the audience were KPA Vice Marshal Kim Il Chol, member of the NDC of the DPRK and minister of the People's Armed Forces, and Choe Thae Bok, Kim Kuk Thae and Kim Ki Nam, secretaries of the Central Committee of the WPK, and Ri Yong Chol and Ri Jae Il, first vice department directors of the Central Committee of the WPK, and KPA Generals Ri Myong Su, Hyon Chol Hae and Pak Jae Gyong.
 The art squads put on the stage colorful numbers of various genres including chorus "Glory to the General", female solo "Soldiers Live Near the General", female chorus "A Magpie Chirps at the Post", mixed chorus "Arirang for Army-People Unity", agitation at soldiers' oath-taking ceremonies "Don't Forget even a Moment What a Soldier Swore ", and singing with oungum "Blue Sky over My Country", mixed chorus and singing "A Soldier Hears Rice Ears to Rustle", chorus and story-telling "Kitchen Cart Runs" and chorus "Song of Comradeship". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Expressing great satisfaction over the splendid performance given by the members of art squads as artistes of the revolutionary army, Kim Jong Il extended high appreciation and thanks to them for having created art pieces of diverse genres with strong militancy and appeal, influence and great attraction and made mobile performance tours to dynamically present them before servicepersons and thereby powerfully encouraging those reliably standing guard over the defence line of the country to implement the military line of the WPK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that art activities are very important for educating soldiers, he set forth tasks which would serve as guidelines in conducting dynamic performance tours to present revolutionary and militant art pieces encouraging servicepersons to wage a heroic struggle and perform feats.
